Congratulations you have beaten Ch.2. Ch.3 gets interesting from here. 2 more levels. 

The next one may not be too hard but the one after...level 5...I cannot imagine how slightly easier it will be on easy mode. 
After beating level 5 that is it UNTIL they release Ch.4 which will come out in Nov or Dec AFTER they release their Dark Deception multiplayer game called : Dark Deception: Monsters and Mortals. 

Which is set to release on Oct 29th with a private public beta signups being on the 9th or 10th. They start on the 16th to the 20th. The game might release before the 29th depending on how the beta does. 

Don't worry. When Ch.4 comes by there will be 3 levels to play instead of 2. 

Ch.4 according to one of the devs is going to be so hard that even good or decent players might need to go to easy mode. 

Good luck against the Dread Duckies in...actually I won't say where. You'll find out soon enough.

text:
Here's my reasoning on why I think Duck is probably one of the top 2 worst levels so far.
1. Monkey business is random, so its a little hard to reliably do, but it's so much shorter than the rest.
2. School is a little longer, but with speed boost, its quite possible and not overly difficult.
3. On deadly decadence, the watchers actually have a predictable AI, and there's an invincible spot so you can analyze and plan your strategy. The maze is a little less predictable, but it's still short enough.
4. The ducks are just really annoying. It gets easier, but the boss battle is a massive pain to deal with, and I've gotten spooked by that duck by the entrance that breaks the wall too many times.
5. This one is real REAL annoying at the beginning, but the middle and end are exploitable. Its long, so there are definitely more chances to screw up, but the boss battle is so much easier than the ducks imo.
I'd probably put the ducks and the circus at the same difficulty, although the game as a whole is pretty hard.
